17. Final summary

In simple terms, the system works like this:

1. take a patient video or pose data
2. estimate body landmarks
3. compute joint angles through time
4. compare the motion with known action references
5. score quality based on similarity, symmetry, and smoothness
6. detect possible stroke-related movement limitations
7. recommend rehabilitation exercises with guidance

So the system is an explainable AI-assisted movement analysis pipeline intended to support physiotherapists in monitoring rehabilitation progress.
